Setup Instructions

1. Go to https://thingspeak.com/ to create Channel and the required details (e.g. field section) in the created Channel

2. Take note of the Channel ID and the Write API Key; you may want to copy and paste these details into the notepad first

3. install the thingspeak library. In terminal, type:

$ sudo apt-get update
$ sudo apt-get upgrade
$ sudo pip install thingspeak
$ sudo pip install requests

##############################################################################################################################
If pip is not installed, follow the following steps and try the above commands again to install thingspeak:
(i) Download the get-pip.py file from https://bootstrap.pypa.io/get-pip.py
(ii) In terminal, type command:
$ curl https://bootstrap.pypa.io/pip/2.7/get-pip.py -o get-pip.py

(iii) Once done, type command to install pip:
$ sudo python get-pip.py

##############################################################################################################################
##############################################################################################################################
If the above still has errors, try the following instead:
(i) Go to the website https://pypi.org/project/thingspeak/#files and download the thingspeak zip file (.tar.gz). Extract the files.

(ii) Change directory to the thingspeak folder
$ cd /pathdirectory

(iii) Run the setup.py file using the below command:
$ sudo python setup.py install

(iv) Go to the website https://pypi.org/project/requests/#files and download the requests zip file (.tar.gz). Extract the files.

(v) Change directory to the request folder
$ cd /pathdirectory

(vi) Run the setup.py file using the below command:
$ sudo python setup.py install
